        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 9:27PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 927 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
northeast of Mulberry, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Jethro...                         Altus...
Mulberry...                       Dyer...
Denning...                        Etna...
Alix...                           Barnes...
Watalula...                       Meg...
Piney...                          Toney...
Locke...                          Fern...
Wiederkehr Village...             Cecil...
Lonelm...                         Ozark...
Cravens...                        Paradise...

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 16 and
42.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
